Distinguished from similar congeners with long S-shaped or whip-shaped sclerite on procursus [
M. delicata (O. Pickard-Cambridge, 1895)
;
M. talamanca Huber, 1997
] by details of procursus ( Figs 633–635 ; curvature of main sclerite; shape of ventral hinged process; small dorsal membranous process) and by female internal genitalia ( Figs 639 , 652–653 ; pore plates close together; specific configuration of receptacle and ducts).
